<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued June 08 at 4:26PM CDT until June 08 at 5:00PM CDT by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 500 PM CDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN CALHOUN COUNTY...
At 425 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Fort McClellan,
moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Anniston, Oxford, Jacksonville, Fort McClellan, Weaver, Dearmanville
and Choccolocco.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
